Package: fairpaprika
Title: PAPRIKA Preference Elicitation for Patient Decision Aids
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Jakub", "Fusiak", , "jakub.fusiak@ibe.med.uni-muenchen.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides tools for implementing PAPRIKA-style preference
    elicitation in patient decision aids and other multi-criteria decision
    analysis workflows. The package supports construction of pairwise
    trade-off question banks, recording of strict and indifferent responses,
    transitive closure of implied preferences, linear-programming-based
    estimation of additive part-worth models, answer revision, and diagnostic
    summaries. Additional experimental modules support uncertainty analysis,
    benchmarking, and shared decision-making reports.
